The paper deals with cross-modal retrieval, which involves computer vision (CV) and information retrieval (IR) techniques. The proposed framework involves semi-supervised learning, which is a common topic in machine learning (LG) and natural language processing (NLP) (CL). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in multimedia (MM) analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.IR, followed by cs.MM, cs.LG, and cs.CL.
